name: Salmon Stew
author: Aeroz
summary: Here is a recipe for a salmon stew with lots of vegetables. This dish is a real hit with young and old. It is easy to prepare and smells wonderful! Serve hot over rice.
ingredients: 2  carrots, sliced, or more to taste
4 (4.5 ounce) salmon fillets, cut into cubes
2 tablespoons chopped fresh parsley, or to taste
directions: Melt butter in a large, heavy pot over medium heat
Add celery, carrots, and leek and cook until they just begin to soften, 4 to 6 minutes
Add water and crumble in bouillon cube
Stir in tomato paste, thyme, and garlic
Cover pot, reduce heat to low, and gently simmer for 10 minutes
Stir salmon cubes into the pot and simmer for another 5 minutes
Add olives and parsley, mixing gently
